.Dd June 24, 2026
.Dt ARPING 8
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm arping
.Nd send ARP requests to a neighbor host
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl c Ar count
.Op Fl w Ar timeout
.Op Fl i Ar interval
.Op Fl S Ar source_ip
.Op Fl U
.Op Fl d
.Op Fl G
.Op Fl C
.Op Fl f
.Op Fl A
.Op Fl b
.Op Fl u Ar unit
.Op Fl q
.Fl I Ar interface
.Ar destination
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
utility sends ARP and/or RARP requests to discover and probe hosts on the local network link.
.Pp
The options are as follows:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl A
Send ARP replies instead of requests.
.It Fl b
Keep broadcasting (do not switch to unicast after first reply).
.It Fl C
Cisco-style output. Prints '!' for a reply and '.' for a timeout.
.It Fl c Ar count
Stop after sending
.Ar count
ARP requests.
.It Fl d
Duplicate address detection (DAD) mode.
.It Fl f
Quit on first reply.
.It Fl G
Use default gateway as target.
.It Fl I Ar interface
Specify network interface to use. This option is required.
.It Fl i Ar interval
Time to wait between requests in milliseconds (default 1000).
.It Fl q
Quiet output.
.It Fl S Ar source_ip
Specify source IP address. Defaults to interface IP.
.It Fl U
Unsolicited ARP mode (updates neighbors' ARP caches).
.It Fl u Ar unit
Time unit for output (ns, us, ms). Default is auto-scaling.
.It Fl w Ar timeout
Time to wait for reply in milliseconds (default 1000).
.El
